command.constant_value: go mod init test; go mod tidy; go run trigger_gh_workflow.go -url=$DEC_XPKUBE_ENDPOINT -inputs=$JSON_PAYLOAD

base_cidr_block.description: Echoes back the base_cidr_block input variable value, for convenience if passing the result of this module elsewhere as an object.

network_cidr_blocks.description: A map from network names to allocated address prefixes in CIDR notation.

networks.description: A list of objects corresponding to each of the objects in the input variable 'networks', each extended with a new attribute 'cidr_block' giving the network's allocated address prefix.

base_cidr_block.description: A network address prefix in CIDR notation that all of the requested subnetwork prefixes will be allocated within.

networks.description: A list of objects describing requested subnetwork prefixes. new_bits is the number of additional network prefix bits to add, in addition to the existing prefix on base_cidr_block.

ai_models.description: list of additional AI model definitions

ai_services.description: A list of Azure AI Services account definitions

aks_extra_node_pools.description: list of aks extra node pool parameters

allow_bgp.description: Allows the use/default behavior of disable_bgp_route_propagation = false on subnets even when using SecureHub2-style hubs.

any_nsg_rule_priority.description: boolean to allow nsg_rules.csv rules to use priorities above 3000. Defaults to false, available for backwards compatibility. Setting to true prevents auto-approval.

api_management.description: a list of azure apim management definitions

app_insights.description: a list of user-defined app insights objects

app_service_plans.description: a list of azure app services definitions

ase_internal_encryption.description: Enable internal encryption on ASE or not

budgets.description: List of budgets to apply to resource groups.

build_base_resources.description: Builds base resources (key vault, key, des, managed_pe subnet). Only considered during shared_vnet non-host(client) builds. Defaults to false - hosts and classic spokes will build these resources.

build_custom_key_vault.description: boolean flag to create custom key vault(90 soft delete days key vault)

cognitive_services.description: a list of azure cognitive service account definitions

container_index.description: points to the desired index in the respective list of cidrs inside net_container map

container_registry.description: a list of azure container registry definitions

cross_region_host_index.description: Determines the index of the cross region host vnet. Hosts will add this to their vnet name; clients will reference said vnet.

data_factory.description: Toggle creating a data factory and related resources.

databricks.description: a list of user-defined databricks objects

deploy_diag_storage.description: boolean flag to signal that a customer managed boot diagnostics storage account should be built. Defaults to false

diag_storage_account_id.description: The ID of the Storage Account where logs should be sent.

disable_watcher.description: Disables network watcher flow logs for peering when no NetworkWatcher exists. Only use for testing.

enable_subscription_diagnostics.description: Boolean flag to enable azure monitor diagnostics on the subscription to be collected. Defaults to false.

environment.description: one of the following environments: [ dev | qa | uat | pt | prod | nonprod | preprod | dr | poc | sit ]

external_federated_credentials.description: user defined external OIDC federated credentials

external_nsg.description: When creating NSG rules, use the provided external NSG name and resource group instead of creating a new one. Only applies to micro contexts, defaults to inherit the parent context's NSG.

external_private_endpoints.description: private endpoints for networks not managed by this terraform module

flowlog_retention_days.description: Days to set network watcher flow log retention to. Default is zero (forever).

forward_law_to_eh.description: This will send the diagnostics of the log analytics workspace to event hub for splunk.

gha_federated_credentials.description: user defined github actions federated credentials

go_live_date.description: Date production environment went or will go live

host_cidr_index.description: Sets the vnet_cidr_index of all subnets, unless otherwise set by the subnet.

host_index.description: Determines the index of the host vnet. Hosts will add this to their vnet name; clients will reference said vnet.

host_prefix.description: Overrides the default `subscription-id-env-region` host name prefix.

ignore_tag_changes.description: if true, ignore tag changes after resource creation. Defaults to false.

inherit.description: Flag to determine if the module should inherit the application_id, environment, and location from the module path.

internal_use.description: Internal Use settings for configuring ExpressCloud-Azure. Should not be modified by users.

is_former_kv_naming_convention.description: boolean flag to signal whether this module call makes use of older key vault naming convention - to ensure backwards compatibility

is_former_log_analytics_workspace_naming.description: boolean flag to signal whether this module call had created a log analytics workspace before they were fully treated as global and can only be built once per subscription

is_former_st_naming_convention.description: boolean flag to signal whether this module call makes use of older storage account naming convention - to ensure backwards compatibility

is_host.description: Flag to determine if this a vnet-only host spoke. Client spokes will use this network for their subnets.

is_hub.description: Disables pe subnet requirement, but preserve other is_spoke functionality. Defaults to false. Hub use only

is_hub_staging.description: Prevents base keyvault and eventhub related resources from being built. Defaults to false. Hub use only

is_peered.description: boolean flag to peer spoke. Defaults to true

is_spoke.description: boolean flag to signal that this is a standard spoke build. If false, all resources are optional, and only what is explicitly defined by the user during module call is built. Defaults to true

kv_locks.description: Toggles keyvault management locks. Defaults to true, security will auto-remediate keyvaults that do not have a lock.

legacy_dr.description: flags whether this dr env had subnets built using infoblox and prior to network address changes after v0.34.3

legacy_standard_kv.description: Flag for legacy builds to prevent recreation of keyvaults with non 'Premium' skus. Defaults to false.

load_balancers.description: a list of load balancer configurations

location.description: one of the following regions: [ eastus2 | centralus | westus3 | eastus ]

log_analytics_workspace.description: Log Analytics Workspaces - choose either "standard" or "custom". In case of custom also pass a log_analytics_workspace_specs variable.

log_analytics_workspace_id.description: Specifies the ID of a Log Analytics Workspace where Diagnostics Data should be sent.

managed_disks.description: list of user managed disks configurations

micro_suffix.description: Suffix to apply to resource names. Only used in a micro.

micro_type.description: Toggles micro call to use outputs from the core context for shared locals and sets restrictions on resources built.

offset.description: An Extension's offset to allow for NSG rules to not collide with other extensions/the spoke

partner_solution_id.description: The ID of the market partner solution where Diagnostics Data should be sent.

peer_external_vnet.description: externally managed vnet in the same subscription to peer with

public_keyvaults.description: Enables public network access on keyvaults. Defaults to false to meet security requirements for new builds.

random_kv_names.description: Keyvault names are randomized at creation. If false, uses the location code naming convention for backwards compatibility.

random_nsg_suffix.description: Flag to determine if the NSG suffix is random, defaults to false to use the directory name.

reader_groups.description: List of AD Group Object IDs that will be granted Reader access to all Resource Groups

recovery_services_vaults.description: a list of azure recovery services vault definitions

required_tags.description: tags required by Hybrid Cloud FinOps - KB0043733

routing_environment.description: Determines the hub that a spoke vnet will peer to. Defaults to prod to preserve current non-prod connectivity to existing hubs.

search_services.description: a list of user-defined Cognitive Search Services

service_bus_entities.description: list of types of service bus entities and their respective configurations

service_bus_subscription_rules.description: list of subscription rules to attatch to a subscription

service_bus_subscriptions.description: list of subscriptions config to attach to topics

snow_dns_env.description: Sets the ServiceNow environment to make DNS requests to. Defaults to Dev.

storage_accounts.description: a list of user-defined storage account objects

subnets.description: list of subnets. subnet egress_type: cisco_firewall | azure_firewall | aks | pci | none --> default = azure_firewall

subscription_diagnostic_objects.description: Diagnostic Objects = { log = [#["Category Name", "Retention Enabled (true/false)", "Retention Period"]] metric = [#["Category Name", "Diagnostic Enabled(true/false)", "Retention Enabled (true/false)", "Retention Period"]]

tag_sets.description: tag overrides that can be applied to resources

use_global_law_fl.description: boolean flag to signal whether to use log-securehub-global-ntwk-flowlogs in the hub, when use_ud_law_fl is false. Defaults to false.

use_spoke_rgs.description: Flag to determine if the main context's resource groups are used.

use_ud_law_fl.description: boolean flag to signal whether to use the log_analytics_workspace for NSG Flow Logs. Defaults to true

virtual_machines.description: a list of virtual machine configurations

vnet_cidr_suffixes.description: determines size of vnet container from infoblox rather than calculate from subnets.
